{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 11:16:59.645764", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of Network Health\\n- Control plane: All EBGP sessions across the Clos fabric are established and stable on all routers tested (leaves, spines, super-spine). No adjacency flaps observed.\\n- Data plane: End-to-end host connectivity between pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24) is failing in both directions (ICMP ping attempts timed out).\\n\\nKey Observations and Evidence\\n1) Host reachability tests\\n- Ping pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1 and pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0 both timed out.\\n- Host IP setups are correct:\\n  - pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2/24 with default gateway 10.0.0.1\\n  - pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2/24 with default gateway 10.0.1.1\\n\\n2) BGP status across fabric\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) peers with spines 172.16.0.4 (AS 65100) and 172.16.0.8 (AS 65101) — both established; each peer shows State/PfxRcd nonzero.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201) peers with spines 172.16.0.6 and 172.16.0.10 — both established; prefixes received as expected.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) both up with super-spine and leaves. Note: spine_router_0_0 shows 0 PfxRcd from super-spine, but it still has correct routes to leaf LANs via its leaf peers; this does not affect the observed failure.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000) has both spine neighbors established and is installing routes for both leaf networks.\\n\\n3) Routing tables (critical finding)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 routing and config:\\n  - Has a static blackhole route: “ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0”\\n  - Is advertising “network 10.0.0.0/24” and also “network 10.0.0.0/30” via BGP.\\n  - Kernel routes include:\\n    - blackhole 10.0.0.0/30\\n    - connected 10.0.0.0/24 via eth2 (10.0.0.1)\\n    - learned 10.0.1.0/24 via spine 172.16.0.4\\n- leaf_router_0_1 routing and config:\\n  - Advertising only “network 10.0.1.0/24” as expected.\\n- Spines and super-spine learning the more-specific 10.0.0.0/30:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1 both install BGP route 10.0.0.0/30 via leaf_router_0_0.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 also installs 10.0.0.0/30 via spine 65100.\\n\\nAnomaly Detected\\n- Misconfigured static blackhole route and BGP advertisement on leaf_router_0_0 for 10.0.0.0/30.\\n- This /30 covers IPs 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3, including host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2). Because /30 is more specific than /24, all traffic destined to 10.0.0.2 is matched by the blackhole on leaf_router_0_0 and dropped.\\n\\nImpact and Symptom Correlation\\n- Forward path pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: packets reach leaf_router_0_0 and traverse the fabric to 10.0.1.0/24 without issue.\\n- Return path pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: routed back to leaf_router_0_0, but because 10.0.0.2 falls within 10.0.0.0/30, the packet is blackholed at leaf_router_0_0, causing ping failure/timeouts.\\n- The advertisement of 10.0.0.0/30 into BGP ensures that all upstream devices prefer this more-specific route and forward traffic destined to 10.0.0.0/30 to leaf_router_0_0, where it is dropped. This creates a deterministic blackhole for pc_0_0.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Fault type: configuration error.\\n- Erroneous lines observed:\\n  - ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0\\n  - router bgp 65200 … address-family ipv4 unicast … network 10.0.0.0/30\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- A misconfigured static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 was added on leaf_router_0_0 and advertised via BGP. Due to longest-prefix-match behavior, this causes all traffic destined for 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) to be routed to and dropped by the blackhole on leaf_router_0_0, breaking host-to-host connectivity.\\n\\nAdditional Notes\\n- The observation that spine_router_0_0 shows PfxRcd=0 from the super-spine neighbor does not contribute to the current outage; spines still have the necessary routes via their leaf neighbors and propagate them fabric-wide.\\n- No evidence of interface down, ARP failure, or service failure. The issue is strictly due to routing preference for the erroneous more-specific prefix., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='aac5dbe3-2476-4694-8f19-6e2a45a5eedb'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
